<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665543>
    dc:description "Figure 12. (a) Copris bicuspis Germar 1824, holotype dorsal habitus. (b) Dorsal habitus of Dichotomius (S.) punctulatipennis (Luederwaldt)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3665543/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665525>
    dc:description "Figure 3. (a) Holotype of Dichotomius (Selenocopris) inachoides (Felsche) (b) Dichotomius (Homocanthonides) smaragdinus (Perty) (c) Holotype of Dichotomius (Dichotomius) prietoi (Martínez)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3665525/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3665529>
    dc:description "Figure 5. (a) Ventral view of the open pygidium of a female of D. ascanius: sixth – sixth ventrite, int – intestine;vgn – approximately location of vagina aperture;spt – spermatecha indicated by white arrow.(b) General dorsal aspect of Cephagonus female genitalia, the elytra and abdominal superior ventrites were removed: pyg – pygidium; spt – spermatheca; spdc – spermatheca duct; spgl – spermatheca gland; bcpl – bursa copulatrix. (c) D. ascanius spermatheca. (d) D. ingens spermatheca. (e) D. fissiceps spermatheca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3665529/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

